    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-12-24T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-12-24T14:00:00-05:00" n="637"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d637">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.6363/99: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-24T13:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 24, 1921—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>141. My despatches 106, 120 and 174.<note n="28" xml:id="d637fn28">None
                        printed.</note> Government has delivered ultimatum to the Costa Rica Oil
                    Corporation demanding immediate reference dispute to sole arbitrator. Oil
                    corporation privately informed President Acosta has announced that he intends to
                    declare forfeiture of corporation and that he has assurance of Department <pb
                        facs="0793" n="669" xml:id="pg_669"/> of State that such action will not be
                    opposed. Please refer to penultimate paragraph of your instruction No. 7
                    December 13, 1920.<note n="29" xml:id="d637fn29">
                        <ref target="frus1920v01#pg_845">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1920, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 845</ref>.</note> Is it desired that the
                    Legation take any action?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
